The intersection of sets A and B, denoted as A ∩ B, consists of the elements that are common to both sets. In this case, the intersection is:

A ∩ B = {2, 3, 4}

The union of sets A and B, denoted as A ∪ B, consists of all the elements from both sets, without repetition. In this case, the union is:

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
